#### DATA ANALYTICS & BUSINESS INTELLIGENCE – TASK 1 REPORT

1. Project Overview
This project focuses on performing Data Cleaning, Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), and
Dashboard Creation using the Superstore dataset. The objective is to extract meaningful insights
and present them using an interactive Power BI dashboard.
2. Objectives
1 Clean and preprocess raw data
2 Perform exploratory data analysis (EDA)
3 Identify key business metrics (KPIs)
4 Build an interactive dashboard in Power BI
5 Generate actionable business insights

3. Tools & Technologies Used
1. Power BI
2 Microsoft Excel / CSV
3 Python (Pandas – optional)
4. Dataset Description

1 Dataset Name: Superstore Dataset
2 Contains information about Orders, Sales, Profit, Customers, Regions, Categories

5. Data Cleaning Process
1 Removed missing/null values
2 Removed duplicate records
3 Converted date columns to proper format
4 Ensured correct data types (numeric, date, text)

6. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
1 Total Sales and Profit calculated
2 Sales distribution across regions
3 Profit analysis by category
4 Time-based sales trends

7. Dashboard Overview (Power BI)
1 KPIs: Total Sales, Total Profit, Total Orders
2 Sales by Region (Bar Chart)
3 Profit by Category (Column Chart)
4 Sales Trend Over Time (Line Chart)
5 Filters: Region, Category, Order Date

8. Key Insights
1 West region generates the highest sales
2 Technology category contributes the highest profit
3 Some categories show low or negative profitability
4 Sales trends indicate seasonal variations

9. Business Recommendations
1 Focus on high-performing regions like West for growth
2 Improve or discontinue low-profit products
3 Optimize pricing and discount strategies
4 Use seasonal trends for better inventory planning

10. Conclusion
This project demonstrates how raw data can be transformed into meaningful insights using data
analytics tools. The Power BI dashboard provides a clear and interactive way to support business
decision-making.
